    ============================================================================
    Platform & Environment
    ============================================================================
 
    OS           : Windows 11 24H2+ (Build 26100+) | Windows Server 2025
    Sysmon       : Native (Windows Optional Feature - KB5077241+)
    Schema       : 4.91
    SIEM         : Wazuh 4.14.0+
    Rule Syntax  : RuleGroup nested (EventFiltering > RuleGroup > EventType)
 
    ============================================================================
    Description
    ============================================================================
 
    Enterprise-grade Sysmon configuration for the Windows Native Sysmon
    feature (Windows Optional Feature). Tuned for high-fidelity threat
    detection with minimal noise, aligned with the MITRE ATT&CK framework
    and optimized for Wazuh ingestion in SOC, Threat Hunting and CSIRT
    workflows.
 
    Key design decisions:
      - All rules use AND logic (groupRelation="and") inside RuleGroup blocks
        to reduce false positives and increase signal precision.
      - Multi-value operators (contains any, is any, excludes any, begin with
        with semicolon-delimited tokens) are used throughout for compact and
        efficient rule definitions supported by Schema 4.91.
      - Excludes are scoped — broad excludes only at the RuleGroup level,
        never inside targeted include Rules.
 
    ============================================================================
    Covered Event IDs
    ============================================================================
 
    EID  1       - ProcessCreate          T1059, T1218, T1003, T1036, T1548
    EID  2       - FileCreateTime         T1070.006
    EID  3       - NetworkConnect         T1571, T1021, T1059
    EID  5       - ProcessTerminate       Suspicious user/temp paths
    EID  6       - DriverLoad             Exclude valid Microsoft-signed
    EID  7       - ImageLoad              T1055 (vaultcli, samlib, cryptdll)
    EID  8       - CreateRemoteThread     T1055
    EID  9       - RawAccessRead          T1006
    EID 10       - ProcessAccess          T1003.001 (LSASS)
    EID 11       - FileCreate             T1547.001, T1053, T1059
    EID 12/13/14 - RegistryEvent          T1547.001, T1543.003, T1562.001
    EID 15       - FileCreateStreamHash   T1564.004 (ADS)
    EID 17/18    - PipeEvent              CobaltStrike default pipes, PSExec
    EID 19/20/21 - WmiEvent               T1546.003
    EID 22       - DnsQuery               T1071.004 (C2 over DNS, TLD-based)
    EID 23       - FileDelete             T1070.004
    EID 24       - ClipboardChange        Exclude browsers and Office apps
    EID 25       - ProcessTampering       T1055.012 (Hollowing, Herpaderping)
    EID 26       - FileDeleteDetected     T1070.004
    EID 29       - FileExecutableDetected T1204 (Downloads, Public paths)
 
    ============================================================================
    Operators Used (Schema 4.91)
    ============================================================================
 
    contains any    Multi-value substring match (OR logic, semicolon-delimited)
    excludes any    Exclude if value matches any token in the list
    is any          Exact match against any value in the list
    is not          Exact negative match (single value)
    begin with      Prefix match — semicolon-delimited tokens supported
    end with        Suffix match — semicolon-delimited tokens supported
    contains        Single substring match
    is              Exact single match
    image           Match on filename only (strips path prefix)
 
    ============================================================================
    Deployment Notes
    ============================================================================
 
    REQUIREMENT : Sysmon Native does NOT coexist with standalone Sysmon.
                  Verify and remove standalone before enabling the feature:
                  > Get-Service sysmon*
                  > sysmon -u force (if standalone is present)
 
    ENABLE      : Enable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName Sysmon
 
    INSTALL     : sysmon -i
    APPLY       : sysmon -c sysmon-win11-native-wazuh.xml
 
    VALIDATE    : .\Check-SysmonHealth.ps1 -ExportReport
                  /scripts/Check-SysmonHealth.ps1 (included in this repo)
 
    VERIFY HASH : (Get-FileHash "C:\Windows\System32\Sysmon\sysmon-win11-native-wazuh.xml" -Algorithm SHA256).Hash
                  Cross-reference with EID 16 in Sysmon/Operational log.
 
    WAZUH RULES : /ruleset/rules/wazuh-server-4.14/
                  Sync rules after config deployment to eliminate blind spots.
 
